            "answer_text": "Gold, internal huge borrowing (semi obligatory ), emission, stripping valuables from churches and museums,   lend lease loans. You got to remember that USSR had a total command economy.  With onset of war the War Efforts was a single economical  objective.  A system was a bit unusual in a way that emission of money in industries was ring fenced from bleeding into consumer market. I e not having a significant effect on inflation. Cash ruble and cashless ruble was almost like a different currency.  With all prices tightly regulated and almost total rationing system for population a normal economics did not work. Also the only bank permitted was a State Sberbank. Therefore State had a free access to all country savings and deposits if necessary. ",
